'''''Kuwait''''' is a group of approximately 40 [[painting]]s made by [[Nabil Kanso]] in 1990-91 on the [[Gulf War]] and [[Iraq]]’s [[invasion of Kuwait]]. The works in the series were first exhibited in [[Kuwait]]<ref>Huwaidi, Sayed: ''Kanso Declares War on War'', [[Al-Watan (Kuwait)|Al-Watan]], April 23, 1992, [http://kuwaitpainting.com/alwatan.html text]</ref> in March – April 1992 at the Free Atelier Art Center<ref>Hamza, Magda: ''Expressions on the Scars of Iraq’s Invasion of Kuwait'', Sawt Al-Kuwait, April 23, 1992, [http://kuwaitpainting.com/sawtalkuwait.html MH tr.text]</ref><ref>Hilmi, Mufida: ''Screams in Brushes and Oils Project the Invasion of Kuwait'', [[Al-Siyasa]], April 4, 1992, [http://kuwaitpainting.com/alsiyasa.html MH]</ref> and traveled in June to [[Caracas]] for a special exhibit at the Palacio de Gobierno in honor of the [[Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah|Emir of Kuwait]]’s visit to Venezuela.<ref>[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]: ''Kanso Kuwait Exhibition: Commitment for Peace'', June 5, 1992, Caracas [http://kuwaitpainting.com/eluniversal.html tr. text]</ref><ref>Tavio, Arnoldo, El Globo, ''Kanso: Compromiso por la Paz'', June 7, 1992, [http://kuwaitpainting.com/elglobo.html AT article]</ref> Then, the exhibition proceeded to [[Geneva]] and was held at the [[International Red Cross and Red Crescent Museum|Red Cross Museum]] in July – August 1992.<ref>”Compromis pour la Paix”, ''Peintures de Nabil Kanso'', La [[Tribune de Genève]], July, 12, Geneva, 1992</ref><ref>[[Kuwait News Agency|Kuna]], July 10, 1992, [http://kuwaitpainting.com/kuna.html k]</ref>

