==Trivia== *They have a total of over a billion views in [[YouTube]]. Total of 300 million streams officially and 550 million streams in [[Spotify]]. *Second and most liked and shared boy band and pop band video posts in [[Facebook]] as of October 2018. *Most watched music artist on [[Vietnam]] as of 2015 according to YouTube. *Best selling international album act and band to date in [[Indonesia]] and [[Philippines]]. *They have 14 UK number ones and 25 Top 10 hits in UK Singles Chart. 8 number ones and 12 Top 4 overall in [[UK Albums Chart]]. *The highest charting non-British group, pop group and [[Ireland|Irish]] group with most number one appearances in the [[UK Singles Chart]] (15). *[[Mark Feehily]] is the highest charting performer from the [[LGBT]] group with most number one appearances in the UK Singles Chart (15). *[[Shane Filan]] is the highest charting solo Irish act with most number one appearances in the UK Singles Chart (16). *They are the only recording artists to win the prestigious [[The Record of the Year|Record Of The Year]] an incredible four times in just seven years. *Only Irish act, pop band, boy band to have two of previous [[Marvel Entertainment|Marvel]] [[Hollywood]] Actors had been cast in two of the lads' music videos. [[Vinnie Jones]] who played as Juggernaut in '[[X-Men: The Last Stand]]' was featured as the Duke Vincent in '[[Bop Bop Baby]]', while [[Ioan Gruffudd]] who played as [[Mr. Fantastic]] in '[[Fantastic Four]] 2005 & 2007' was featured as one of the high class customers in '[[Uptown Girl]]'. *Most Entries at Number 1 by a Debuting Act. *Only music act to have four number one in UK Singles Chart in only a year. *The first and only artist to have every single from their album reach number-one on the singles chart was Westlife with ''[[Westlife (album)|Westlife]]''. *Only male group with most original songs in an album went straight to number one in UK Singles Chart with four singles. *Biggest-selling single in a week one by a debut artist. *The first pop band and boy band to hit the #1 with its first two singles. *Fastest number one music chart act and band in UK history beating [[Elvis Presley]]'s previous record of three years versus 23 months of Westlife getting each its first seven number-one singles. *Shortest music act or band to have ten or double-figures number ones in the UK Singles Chart (2 years and 10 months - 149 weeks) - more than 3 months quicker than [[The Beatles]] (165 weeks). *First official number one single music act in the 21st century of UK Singles Chart. *Last official number one single music act in the 20th century of UK Singles Chart. *First official number one music artist, band and single in the [[UK Official Download Chart]]. *Highest leaper in the history of Official UK Singles Chart (from #200 to #1) for their single "[[Brandy (Scott English and Richard Kerr song)|Mandy]]". *Second highest leaper as well in history of UK Singles Chart (#194 to #1) with the group's single "[[Unbreakable (Westlife song)|Unbreakable]]". *Most number ones with different albums by a music album act, group, pop group and male group in UK Albums Chart in the 2000s. *Second most number ones, tied with [[Rod Stewart]], with different albums by a music album act, group, pop group and male group in UK Albums Chart clustered per decade since The Beatles in the 1960s. *Second music act to have the longest string of number ones in UK history. *Three of their studio albums were part of the 50 fastest selling albums of all time in UK. *The first Irish act to have both album and single as number one on the same week in the UK charts with their album ''[[Face to Face (Westlife album)|Face to Face]]'' and ''[[You Raise Me Up]]'' single. *Second Irish act to headline concerts in the third largest stadium in [[Europe]], [[Croke Park]], just after [[U2]]. *Biggest arena act of all time in the United Kingdom. *Last concert was the biggest live attendees in a last performance date by a pop act. *Their last concert was the eleventh largest attendance at an outdoor stadium worldwide. *Most performed professional and international music act in X Factor UK. *Only pop band to be invited to perform live in front of a pope and a sultan. *Third highest band, and highest pop band with most number ones and top tens in UK Singles Chart. *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits in the UK: Westlife (22), Runner-up: [[Elvis Presley]] (20) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits by a group in the UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits by a male group in the UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits including debut single by an act in UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits including debut single by a pop group in UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits including debut single by a group in UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits including debut single by male group in UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 5 hits including debut single by pop act in UK: Westlife (22) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits in UK: [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]] (35), Runner-up: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits by a group in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits by a male group in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits including debut single by a group in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits including debut single by male group in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits including debut single by an act in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits including debut single by a pop group in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Consecutive Top 10 hits including debut single by pop act in UK: Westlife (25) *Most Top 40 Hits by a group in UK: [[The Supremes]] (30), Runner-up: [[Take That]] (28), Westlife (26) *Most Top 40 Hits by a male group in UK: Take That (28), Runner-up: Westlife (26) *Most Consecutive Number 1 hits by a group in UK: Westlife (7) *Most Consecutive Number 1 hits by a male group in UK: Westlife (7) *Most Consecutive Number 1 hits by a